{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id52455679-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s252"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"252"},"text":"§ 252.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Tenure and salaries of judges","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Judges of the Court of International Trade shall hold office during good behavior. Each shall receive a salary at an annual rate determined under section 225 of the Federal Salary Act of 1967 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t2/s351–361"},"text":"2 U.S.C. 351–361","children":[],"tail":"), as adjusted by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s461"},"text":"section 461 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id5245567a-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646"},"text":"June 25, 1948, ch. 646","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/899"},"text":"62 Stat. 899","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1955-03-02/ch9/s1/f"},"text":"Mar. 2, 1955, ch. 9, § 1(f)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/69/10"},"text":"69 Stat. 10","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/426/tIV/s403/f"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–426, title IV, § 403(f)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1964-08-14"},"text":"Aug. 14, 1964","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/78/434"},"text":"78 Stat. 434","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/82/tII/s205/b/6"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–82, title II, § 205(b)(6)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-08-09"},"text":"Aug. 9, 1975","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/89/423"},"text":"89 Stat. 423","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/417/tV/s502"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–417, title V, § 502","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-10"},"text":"Oct. 10, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/1742"},"text":"94 Stat. 1742","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id5245567b-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id5245567c-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 296 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s187/a"},"text":"Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 187(a)","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1940-10-10/ch843/s1"},"text":"Oct. 10, 1940, ch. 843, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/54/1101"},"text":"54 Stat. 1101","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1946-07-31/ch704/s1"},"text":"July 31, 1946, ch. 704, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/716"},"text":"60 Stat. 716","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This section contains a part of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s296"},"text":"section 296 of title 28","children":[],"tail":", U.S.C., 1940 ed., Other provisions of such section are incorporated in sections 251, 253, 254, 456, 1581, 2071, 2639, and 2640 of this title."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A provision exempting judge’s salaries from section 1790 of the Revised Statutes was omitted, as such section was repealed by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-26/ch689/s1"},"text":"act Aug. 26, 1935, ch. 689, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/864"},"text":"49 Stat. 864","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A provision for monthly salary payments was omitted since time of payment is a matter for administrative determination.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Changes were made in phraseology.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id5245567d-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id5245567e-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 225 of the Federal Salary Act of 1967, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/206/s225"},"text":"section 225 of Pub. L. 90–206","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1967-12-16"},"text":"Dec. 16, 1967","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/81/642"},"text":"81 Stat. 642","children":[],"tail":", which is classified to chapter 11 (§ 351 et seq.) of Title 2, The Congress."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id5245567f-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/417"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–417","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Judges of the Court of International Trade” for “Judge of the Customs Court”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1975—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/82"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–82","children":[],"tail":" substituted provision that each judge shall receive a salary at an annual rate determined under section 225 of the Federal Salary Act of 1967, as adjusted by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s461"},"text":"section 461 of this title","children":[],"tail":", for provision that each judge shall receive a salary of $30,000 a year."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1964—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/426"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–426","children":[],"tail":" increased salaries of judges from $22,500 to $30,000 a year."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1955—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1955-03-02"},"text":"Mar. 2, 1955","children":[],"tail":", increased salaries of judges from $15,000 to $22,500 a year."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id52455680-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id52455681-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1980 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/417"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–417","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-11-01"},"text":"Nov. 1, 1980","children":[],"tail":", and applicable with respect to civil actions pending on or commenced on or after such date, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/417/s701/a"},"text":"section 701(a) of Pub. L. 96–417","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s251"},"text":"section 251 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id52455682-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1964 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/426"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–426","children":[],"tail":" effective on first day of first pay period which begins on or after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1964-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1964","children":[],"tail":", except to the extent provided in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/426/s501/c"},"text":"section 501(c) of Pub. L. 88–426","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/426/s501"},"text":"section 501 of Pub. L. 88–426","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id52455683-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1955 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1955-03-02"},"text":"Mar. 2, 1955","children":[],"tail":", effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1955-03-01"},"text":"Mar. 1, 1955","children":[],"tail":", see section 5 of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1955-03-02"},"text":"Mar. 2, 1955","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t2/s4501"},"text":"section 4501 of Title 2","children":[],"tail":", The Congress."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id52455684-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id52455685-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Salary Increases","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For adjustment of salaries of judges under this section, see the executive order detailing the adjustment of certain rates of pay set out as a note under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5332"},"text":"section 5332 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":", Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For prior year salary increases per the recommendation of the President, see Prior Salary Recommendations notes under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t2/s358"},"text":"section 358 of Title 2","children":[],"tail":", The Congress."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For miscellaneous provisions dealing with adjustments of pay and limitations on use of funds to pay salaries in prior years, see notes under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5318"},"text":"section 5318 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":", Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Salaries of presiding judge and associate judges increased from $10,000 to $15,000 a year by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1946-07-31/ch704/s1"},"text":"act July 31, 1946, ch. 704, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/716"},"text":"60 Stat. 716","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Salaries of presiding judge and associate judges increased from $9,000 to $10,000 a year by the Tariff Act of 1930, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1930-06-17/ch497/tIV/s518"},"text":"act June 17, 1930, ch. 497, title IV, § 518","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/46/737"},"text":"46 Stat. 737","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],